one-period price \eqn{e^{-y^{(1)}_{t+s}}} equals
\eqn{\exp(-m(\mathrm{step}) y^{(\mathrm{step})}_{t+s} / 100)}, the
step-maturity (one-period) bond at date \eqn{t + s}.
